## Purpose
`RegionRecord` is the runtime’s internal representation of a region. It encodes the structured concurrency ownership tree and the conditions for quiescent close.

## Core Fields (Plan-of-Record)
```rust
pub struct RegionRecord {
    pub id: RegionId,
    pub parent: Option<RegionId>,

    pub children: HashSet<TaskId>,
    pub subregions: HashSet<RegionId>,

    pub state: RegionState,
    pub budget: Budget,
    pub cancel: Option<CancelReason>,

    /// LIFO stack
    pub finalizers: Vec<Finalizer>,

    pub policy: Policy,
    pub name: Option<String>,
}
```

## Finalizers
- Stored in registration order; executed LIFO.
- Must run during region close after draining children.

## Arena Storage
Use the internal `Arena<RegionRecord>` (no external slab dependency).

## Required Invariants
- INV-TREE
- INV-QUIESCENCE
- INV-CANCEL-PROPAGATES
- INV-DEADLINE-MONOTONE

## Acceptance Criteria
- Region tree links are consistent.
- Region close gating checks:
  - children terminal
  - subregions closed
  - obligations resolved
  - finalizers complete

