 {"id":"asupersync-9uy4","title":"Add Cx API for cancel attribution access","description":"## Overview

Add methods to Cx for accessing detailed cancellation attribution.

## API Additions

```rust
impl Cx {
    /// Cancel this region with a detailed reason.
    /// 
    /// # Example
    /// ```
    /// cx.cancel_with(CancelKind::User, "User pressed Ctrl+C");
    /// ```
    pub fn cancel_with(&self, kind: CancelKind, message: impl Into<String>);

    /// Get the cancellation reason if this region is cancelled.
    /// 
    /// Returns None if not cancelled.
    /// 
    /// # Example
    /// ```
    /// if let Some(reason) = cx.cancel_reason() {
    ///     println!("Cancelled: {:?}", reason.kind);
    /// }
    /// ```
    pub fn cancel_reason(&self) -> Option<&CancelReason>;

    /// Iterate through the full cancellation cause chain.
    /// 
    /// The first element is the immediate reason, followed by
    /// parent causes in order (immediate -> root).
    /// 
    /// # Example
    /// ```
    /// for cause in cx.cancel_chain() {
    ///     println!("  - {:?} at region {:?}", cause.kind, cause.origin_region);
    /// }
    /// ```
    pub fn cancel_chain(&self) -> impl Iterator<Item = &CancelReason>;

    /// Get the root cause of cancellation.
    /// 
    /// This is the original trigger, regardless of how many
    /// parent regions the cancellation propagated through.
    /// 
    /// Returns None if not cancelled.
    pub fn root_cancel_cause(&self) -> Option<&CancelReason>;

    /// Check if cancellation was due to a specific kind.
    /// 
    /// This checks the immediate reason, not the cause chain.
    pub fn cancelled_by(&self, kind: CancelKind) -> bool;

    /// Check if any cause in the chain is a specific kind.
    /// 
    /// Useful for checking if a timeout anywhere in the parent
    /// hierarchy caused this cancellation.
    pub fn any_cause_is(&self, kind: CancelKind) -> bool;
}
```

## Usage Example

```rust
async fn handle_request(cx: &Cx) -> Result<Response, Error> {
    match do_work(cx).await {
        Outcome::Ok(response) => Ok(response),
        Outcome::Cancelled(_) => {
            // Log detailed attribution
            if let Some(reason) = cx.cancel_reason() {
                tracing::info!(
